msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:111
msgid "General Deployment Considerations"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:113
msgid ""
"It is important to appreciate the use-case or use-cases for which you "
"wish to deploy Kolab, and map that to the appropriate deployment "
"scenario."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:116
msgid ""
"After all, Kolab Groupware is Made To Measure, and supremely flexible. It"
" is best deployed after you articulate what you seek to get out of it -- "
"especially for businesses."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:121
msgid "Generic Statements"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:123
msgid ""
"Larger numbers of users make it more important to ensure service "
"availability."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:126
msgid ""
"Larger numbers of users make load-balancing (and high-availability "
"through load-balancing) more attractive, more efficient and more cost-"
"effective."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:130
msgid ""
"Contrary to popular belief, larger numbers of users make capacity "
"planning more unpredictable, up to next to near impossible. Here, you "
"require the ability to scale up and down as *turns out to be needed*, and"
" not be locked into a certain scale with limited options to break out."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:136
msgid ""
"Should running an extra couple of virtual machine be relatively cheap, "
"then you are likely looking for :ref:`deployment_multi-server-for-each-"
"service`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:140
msgid ""
"The larger the (potential) data footprint, the more important it becomes "
"to consider your storage options."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:143
msgid "The more flexibility you require in scaling;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:145
msgid "the more likely you run idle over-capacity, or"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:147
msgid "under-performing services because of under-capacity, but"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:149
msgid "the easier it is to answer either of the aforementioned problems."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:152
msgid ""
"the more you need means to adapt quickly, preferably automated, by which "
"we mean infrastructure services such as provisioning and configuration "
"management services."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:157
msgid "A Couple of Users"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:159
msgid ""
"In terms of capacity, for a family server, SOHO situation or micro- "
"entity, it is probably more than sufficient to run :doc:`localhost`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:162
msgid ""
"If the data is really important, and you do not have data redundancy "
"built into the single server (through RAID, or regular backups that are "
"easy to restore), such an environment might want to opt for a :doc"
":`redundant-server`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:168
msgid "Dozens of Users"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:170
msgid ""
"When a deployment seeks to serve groupware to dozens of users, "
":doc:`localhost` suffices unless the average user's usage pattern is "
"extremely high."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:174
msgid ""
"A Free Software ISV with employees working remotely, from home, for "
"example, very much relies on electronic communications. Operating in the "
"Free Software community, it's communication patterns are ever increasing,"
" with its employees subscribing to upstream communities' mailing lists, "
"and the organization itself possibly providing services to its community."
" These would be considered *keyboard-bound users*."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:181
msgid ""
"While servicing only a couple of dozen users, the number of messages "
"exchanged easily exceeds thousands per day."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:184
msgid ""
"For such a deployment, you may consider a deployment scenario as depicted"
" in :ref:`deployment_multi-server-with-combined-services`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:187
msgid ""
"In contrast, if your dozens of users are actually plumbers, carpenters, "
"firemen, airline pilots or otherwise regularly distracted from the "
"keyboard and monitor, :doc:`localhost` may suffice -- although your users"
" may in this case be synchronizing their mobile devices, significantly "
"increasing the usage pattern outside of their presence at the keyboard."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:194
msgid ""
"Scaling up from a single server deployment to a deployment with multiple "
"servers is relatively straight-forward, but, depending on what service "
"you choose to migrate off of the single host, possibly involves data "
"migration, some down-time, and configuration changes. As such, such "
"migrations require sufficient preparation and planning."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:200
msgid ""
"Suffice it to say that also, should you find the deployment type you "
"choose initially underperforms, user acceptance of the solution may very "
"well be negatively impacted -- sometimes beyond repair."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst
msgid "Todo"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:206
msgid ""
"Somewhere other than here, document the process of scaling up from one "
"single server on to multiple servers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:212
msgid "Hundreds of Users"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:214
msgid ""
"Providing Kolab Groupware to hundreds of users is an environment of some "
"scale. The starting point is likely :ref:`deployment_multi-server-with-"
"combined-services`, however;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:218
msgid "You may already have centralized authentication and authorization,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:220
msgid ""
"You probably already have an existing infrastructure, possibly including "
"a perimeter network."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:223
msgid "To illustrate why this is important:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:225
msgid ""
"The Kolab web interfaces do not require a dedicated web server -- if you "
"have one already, then you may want to consider installing the Kolab web "
"interfaces on that, if not simply for the fact that public IP space is "
"limited."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:230
msgid ""
"Other considerations come into play deploying Kolab Groupware, and those "
"are included in the following sections:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:233
msgid ":ref:`deployment-hundreds-redundancy`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:234
msgid ":ref:`deployment-hundreds-high-availability`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:235
msgid ":ref:`deployment-hundreds-load-balancing`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:236
msgid ":ref:`deployment-hundreds-scalability`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:241
msgid "Redundancy"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:243
msgid ""
"Redundancy -- with regards to data -- is a matter to be considered "
"separate from high-availability."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:246
msgid ""
"There are separate, distinct replication levels and scenarios one can "
"consider, and storage devices types to be taken in to account."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:249
msgid ""
"Generally, the largest volume of data is in IMAP spools. These are also "
"very I/O intensive -- much more so than CPU- or memory-intensive."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:252
msgid ""
":ref:`deployment-storage-redundancy` in storage has it's own deployment "
"guide section."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:258
msgid "High-Availability"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:260
msgid ""
"Nothing overloads a helpdesk more than hundreds of users calling in at "
"very much the same point in time, because a service is unavailable (and "
"might, as a domino effect, render other services unavailable)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:264
msgid ""
"The larger your userbase, the more important it is to ensure services "
"remain available -- even during planned service windows."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:267
msgid "A typical approach is to provide \"two of each\"."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:272
msgid "Load-Balancing"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:274
msgid ""
"To use the term load-balancing is to describe the act of providing enough"
" instances of each service to supply enough capacity to deal with the "
"demand on said service. This is separate from the time-window of such "
"demand, however -- the time-window demands scaling, scaling demands load-"
"balancing."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:280
msgid ""
"Load-balacing is where Kolab Groupware shines, since any of the service "
"components can be split up in such many roles as well. Therefore, each "
"quantitively meaningful difference in demand for a given service in a "
"particular role can be scaled up and down as is needed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:288
msgid "Scalability"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:290
msgid ""
"With a quota of 1GB, a total data footprint of 100GB - 900GB is still "
"manageable, but should your users (be allowed to) have larger mailboxes "
"and/or use the File Storage features in Kolab, you are more likely "
"speaking to the tune of several terabytes (if not right from the start, "
"you'll likely get there over time)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:296
msgid ""
"**This** is yet another area were scalability comes into play. One could "
"start with a single Cyrus IMAP server, like so:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:312
msgid ""
"You will want to make sure your users' desktop applications, and the rest"
" of the Kolab software uses a DNS entry to connect to IMAP (for example, "
"``imap.example.org``), so that it is easier for you to change what it is "
"they actually end up connecting to."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:317
msgid ""
"With several terabytes of data, *when* you get there, the desired "
"scenario might look like:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:342
msgid ""
"This is a simple change that can be prepared ahead of time, and "
"implemented during a service window, if and/or when it is needed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:347
msgid ""
"You have options with regards to the target topology of the Cyrus IMAP "
"Murder. Please refer to :ref:`deployment_imap_cyrus-imap-murder`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:352
msgid "A Thousand Users"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:354
msgid ""
"The magical boundary of a thousand users depicts each individual user's "
"usage pattern becomes unpredictable, as for one the number of mobile "
"devices they synchronize are not necessarily under control any longer."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:358
msgid ""
"Generally, the same facets apply as they do for :ref:`deployment-guide-"
"hundreds-of-users`, just with higher load, more storage, more stringent "
"requirements, likely resulting in the need for :ref:`deployment_multi-"
"server-for-each-service`, at least partly -- some services may still be "
"combined."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:364
msgid ""
"Despite a number of users that is likely larger than the majority of "
"Kolab installations, it is still well within the boundaries of normal "
"operations, and should not require any specialist attention."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:368
msgid ""
"Yet, environments of this size and over will want to perform a Proof- of-"
"Concept environment to familiarize themselves with the inner workings of "
"Kolab Groupware, assess the viability of Kolab particulars for large "
"numbers of users stuck with particular work-flows and their system "
"administrator's ability to effectively maintain the infrastructure with "
"this new technology (monitoring, alerting, trending, configuration "
"management, reporting, etc.)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:377
msgid "Several Thousands of Users"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:379
msgid ""
"The larger the enterprise (or: the larger the number of users), the more "
"significant capacity planning becomes in relation to deploying Kolab."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:382
msgid ""
"We have mentioned before that provided a larger number of users, capacity"
" planning becomes a more volatile subject and can be less accurately "
"determined. However, with larger numbers of users, laws of averages come "
"in to play, and the ability to scale with demand can be facilitated -- a "
"margin of error becomes manageable."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:388
msgid ""
"Several thousands of users are typically deployed using a :ref"
":`deployment_multi-server-for-each-service` scenario. Organizations are "
"strongly encouraged to contact `Kolab Systems AG`_ for their services."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:394
msgid "Tens of Thousands of Users"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:396
msgid ""
"The differences between \"tens\" and \"hundreds\" of thousands of users "
"are negligible with regards to the general deployment scenario."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:399
msgid ""
"A clear distinction is often having spread various areas of responsibily "
"for the infrastructure across multiple teams or departments, each of them"
" eligible to resist change making their jobs more involved, and/or not "
"all of them as familiar or comfortable with the introduction of new "
"technology in their respective stacks."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:406
msgid "Hundreds of Thousands of Users"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:408
msgid ""
"When an enterprise with 350.000 employees plans for a Kolab deployment, "
"it is unlikely all of the users will be migrated over the course of a "
"single service window, and despite what other groupware vendors might "
"tell you, it is near to impossible to accurately plan for the capacity "
"required."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:414
msgid ""
"It is also important to appreciate any existing infrastructure and "
"network topology, and for Kolab to integrate into that environment."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:417
msgid ""
"Ranging from small and medium-sized business, large enterprise and "
"service provider deployments, the number of users involved ranges from 50"
" to anywhere in the hundreds of thousands or millions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:424
msgid "Organizations with Multiple Domain Namespaces"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:426
msgid ""
"When the people throughout an organization use different email domains, "
"but need to maintain the ability to share groupware data with everyone "
"else in the organization, it is important to appreciate the effects of "
"using the primary recipient email address (*mail*) of the user as the "
"authorization ID (*result_attribute*)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:432
msgid ""
"This might be the case in a holding with multiple subsidiaries. To "
"illustrate, an example holding corporation **Holding, Inc.**, with "
"subsidiaries *Foo, Inc.* and *Bar, Inc.*:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:445
msgid ""
"This is not considered a case for ISPs or providers of Hosted Kolab, but "
"may be applicable to **customers** of ISPs and **consumers** of Hosted "
"Kolab. ISPs and Hosted Kolab providers should refer to dedicated "
"sections:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:450
msgid ":ref:`deployment_hosted-kolab`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:452
msgid "Let's suppose that:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:454
msgid "People working for *Holding, Inc.* use email addresses ``@holding.inc``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:457
msgid "People working for *Foo, Inc.* use email addresses ``@foo.inc``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:459
msgid "People working for *Bar, Inc.* use email addresses ``@bar.inc``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:461
msgid "And:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:463
msgid ""
"All people are contained within a single LDAP tree (for, perhaps, Human "
"Resources is a department within the holding, providing services to the "
"holding as well as its subsidiaries, like it is providing Kolab Groupware"
" services in this example):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:478
msgid ""
"In a default Kolab Groupware installation, the following mailboxes might "
"be created:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:481
msgid "user/john.doe@holding.inc"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:482
msgid "user/jim.smith@holding.inc"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:483
msgid "user/joe.average@foo.inc"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:484
msgid "user/jane.roe@bar.inc"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:486
msgid ""
"Because Cyrus IMAP uses the email domain as an authorization realm, and "
"no cross-realm authorization is allowed, in this scenario, John, Joe and "
"Jane cannot share mailboxes - though John and Jim can."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:490
msgid ""
"This may be the desired effect, and if it is, you can skip reading the "
"rest of this topic."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:493
msgid ""
"If it is not the intended effect however, and you seek to allow all "
"people to share groupware data with all other users, you must consider "
"the following:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:497
msgid ""
"Should all people be given a primary recipient email address of "
"``@holding.inc``, in an attempt to make all users end up in the same "
"authorization realm, then they are implicitly allowed to send using that "
"email address."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:502
msgid "This in itself may not be desirable."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:504
msgid ""
"To enable users to share groupware data while their primary recipient "
"email addresses make them end up in different authorization realms, you "
"should set the ``result_attribute`` setting in **kolab.conf(5)** to the "
"name of an attribute that does not contain a realm identifier (i.e. "
"something without an '@' in it), such as the ``uid`` attribute, which by "
"default does not include a domain name space. This would create the "
"following mailboxes (if the surname is used for the uid attribute):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:512
msgid "user/average"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:513
msgid "user/doe"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:514
msgid "user/roe"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:515
msgid "user/smith"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:517
msgid ""
"You may also consider setting ``virtdomains`` to ``off`` in "
"**imapd.conf(5)**, although this implies only the null realm is ever "
"going to be used."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment-guide/index.rst:521
msgid ""
"For larger deployments, we also recommend reading about :ref"
":`deployment_imap_cyrus-imap-murder`."
msgstr ""

